@url=http://localhost:5000/api/books

### Test Case 1: Search for a book from Open Library API (without importing)
GET {{url}}/search/harry potter
Content-Type: application/json

### Test Case 2: Search for another book
GET {{url}}/search/White Fang?limit=5
Content-Type: application/json

### Test Case 3: Import a book directly from Open Library to database
POST {{url}}/import/White Fang
Content-Type: application/json

### Test Case 4: Import another book
POST {{url}}/import/harry potter and the philosopher's stone
Content-Type: application/json

### Test Case 5: Search for a book that doesn't exist
GET {{url}}/search/nonexistentbooktitle12345
Content-Type: application/json

### Test Case 6: Try to import a book that doesn't exist
POST {{url}}/import/nonexistentbooktitle12345
Content-Type: application/json

### Test Case 7: Verify imported books are in your database
GET {{url}}/
Content-Type: application/json
